Reasoning: The paper deals with the tradeoff between performance and channel state information feedback in a communication system, which is a core topic in information theory (cs.IT) and communication systems (cs.COMM). The use of encoding and decoding with a phase-Markov structure suggests a focus on system design and optimization, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The consideration of feedback quality and timeliness also suggests a focus on network protocols and algorithms, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the consideration of block and non-block fading channel models suggests a focus on signal processing and machine learning, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
